South Africa’s ANC’s Johannesburg region Chair, Geoff Makhubo, is the new Mayor of the City of Johannesburg. Makhubo got 137 of the 268 votes cast, making him the new mayor of Africa's economic powerhouse. Opposition’s Democratic Alliance’s Mayoral Committee Member for Finance, Funzela Ngobeni received 101 votes while the Economic Freedom Fighter’s Regional Chair, Musa Novela received 30 votes. Former Johannesburg Mayor, Herman Mashaba, officially left office at the end of November. ANC National Spokesperson, Pule Mabe, has urged South Africans to respect and support the leadership of Makhubo as they respected Mashaba. --SABC--